title: Nebraska Sinkhole Swallows Two Cars At Busy Intersection | 10 News
description: Two vehicles have been partially swallowed by a sinkhole that suddenly opened at a Nebraska intersection while they were stopped at traffic lights.  Traffic camera vision from Omaha shows the ground giving way without warning, leaving both cars nose-up in the crater as bystanders rushed to help.  Local reports say no one was injured, with both drivers climbing out before emergency crews arrived.  Omaha Police have closed the road in both directions for several days, warning the sinkhole could expand.
